        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Moses Austin to Joseph Nye &amp; Sons, New York.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            


<p><placeName>Louisiana Territory </placeName>                       <placeName>Hereulaneum </placeName><date when="1810-03-15">15th March 1810</date>&#8212;</p>

<p>$1768</p>

<p>For value received of <persName>Seth W Nye</persName>, I promise to pay <persName>Joseph Nye
and Son</persName> or order Seventeen hundred and Sixty Eight dollars at<pb n="171"/>
the <placeName>City of New York</placeName> in Ninety days after date with usual grace,
for which I have signed Triplicate Notes all of this tenor and date
One of which is to remain in full force and virtue the other two
to stand void&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Moses Austin</persName>    [Rubric]</p>
<p>Pay <persName>Messrs Hicks Jenkins and Co</persName> the within note</p>

<p><persName>Joseph Nye</persName>    [Rubric]</p>
<p>Rec payment in <persName>Henry Austin</persName> Dft on <persName>E and A Townsend</persName> at 30
days&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Hicks Jenkins &amp; C°</persName>    [Rubric]</p>
<p><date when="1810-06-24">June 24.1810</date></p>

<p>[Endorsed:] Note paid <persName>S W Nye</persName></p>
<p>1768$</p>
<p>paid in <placeName>New York</placeName> and
Charges <persName>John Butler</persName></p>


        </div1>
    </body>
